# SuprSend CLI Project Structure

The SuprSend CLI is a Go-based command-line tool for interacting with the SuprSend API.

## Main Entry Point
- The CLI starts from [main.go](mdc:cmd/suprsend/main.go), which calls `commands.Execute()` from [root.go](mdc:internal/commands/root.go).

## Command Registration
- The root command and global flags are defined in [root.go](mdc:internal/commands/root.go).
- Subcommands are registered in the `init()` functions of files in [internal/commands/](mdc:internal/commands).
- Example: The MCP server command is defined in [startMcpServer.go](mdc:internal/commands/startMcpServer.go).
- User-related commands are defined in [user.go](mdc:internal/commands/user.go).

## Configuration
- Configuration is managed via [config.go](mdc:internal/config/config.go) and uses Viper for config file and environment variable support.
- The default config file is `$HOME/.suprsend.yaml`, but a sample config is provided as [ss.yaml](mdc:ss.yaml) in the project root.

## Utilities
- Output formatting and SDK initialization are handled in [outpututil.go](mdc:internal/utils/outpututil.go) and [sdk_instance.go](mdc:internal/utils/sdk_instance.go).
- The CLI banner is printed from [banner.go](mdc:internal/utils/banner.go).

## Tools and MCP Server
- Tools for the MCP server are defined and registered in [tools.go](mdc:internal/tools/tools.go) and [documentation.go](mdc:internal/tools/documentation.go).
- The MCP server and its tool listing are managed in [startMcpServer.go](mdc:internal/commands/startMcpServer.go).

## Management Code
- The [mgmnt/](mdc:mgmnt) directory contains management and client-related code, such as [client.go](mdc:mgmnt/client.go).

## Documentation
- The [docs/](mdc:docs) directory contains Markdown documentation for CLI commands and usage.

## Scripts and Build Artifacts
- The [scripts/](mdc:scripts) directory contains helper scripts for development or CI.
- The [dist/](mdc:dist) directory is used for build artifacts and distribution outputs.

## Usage
- See [README.md](mdc:README.md) for installation and usage instructions.
